Vietnamese-ish Chicken

**slightly adapted from Serious Eats**

https://www.seriouseats.com/vietnamese-style-baked-chicken-recipe

  - 2 lbs skin-on bone-in chicken thighs
  - 0.25 cups soy sauce
  - 0.25 cups fish sauce
  - 0.25 cups brown sugar
  - 2 tbsp neutral oil
  - 3 tbsp minced ginger
  - 3 tbsp minced garlic
  - 3 tbsp sambal oelek chile sauce
  - optional: 2 tbsp chopped cilantro (_some_ folks been known to think it tastes like soap. ahem.)


  (1) Add all but chicken thighs to bowl and whisk until combined into marinade
  (2) Add chicken thighs to ziploc bag, add combined marinade, let sit between 45 min & 3 hrs
  (3) Remove chicken thighs to wire rack and cook in oven at 425 for ~35 minutes
